summaries.short: After winning a stand-up competition, comedians Mark Viera and Alex Carabano perform in front of a live audience in this Entre Nos special.
summaries.full: After winning a stand-up competition held in conjunction with the New York Latino Film Festival, comedians Mark Viera and Alex Carabano perform in front of a live audience in this Entre Nos special. In these sets, Viera talks about getting in trouble from innocent social media posts, and more; while Carabano shares anecdotes about being short, astrology and dating.

summaries.short: Join comedians Ian Lara and Chris Estrada for a West Coast and East Coast showdown in this HBO Latino comedy special.
summaries.full: Join comedians Ian Lara and Chris Estrada for a West Coast and East Coast showdown in this HBO Latino comedy special.

summaries.short: Comedians Marlena Rodriguez and Kim Congdon each take the stage for this stand-up comedy special.
summaries.full: Comedians Marlena Rodriguez and Kim Congdon perform in front of a live audience in this edition of HBO Latino's Entre Nos stand-up specials. Playful and fast-paced, the show features a lot of commentary on dating and hooking up, from the perspective of some of the funniest working comics today who, yes, also happen to be Latina!

summaries.short: Performances by the winners of New York Latino Film Festival's Annual Latino Stand-Up! Comedy Competition: Cisco Duran and Abi Sanchez.
summaries.full: In this second edition of HBO's and New York Latino Film Festival's Annual Latino Stand-Up! Comedy Competition, Cisco Duran and Abi Sanchez are introduced as the winners. Duran, a Miami native, offers his hilarious perspective on the pros and cons of being Black and Dominican, while Chicagoan Sanchez opens up about his identity struggles and more.

summaries.short: This installment in the "Entre Nos" comedy series features comedians Crystian Ramirez, Vanessa Gonzalez, Rojo Perez and Erik Rivera.
summaries.full: Recorded before a live audience at The Alex Theater in California, this one-hour installment in the "Entre Nos" comedy series spotlights four comedians who really get the Latino experience: Crystian Ramirez, Vanessa Gonzalez, Rojo Perez and Erik Rivera.

summaries.short: Comedians Ramon Rivas, Gina Brillon, Jesus Sepulveda and Nick Guerra perform stand-up in this fifth installment of 'Entre Nos.'
summaries.full: The world's top Latino comics come together for an hour of stand-up comedy in this fifth installment of 'Entre Nos.' Comedians Ramon Rivas, Gina Brillon, Jesus Sepulveda and Nick Guerra share uproarious personal stories in front of a live audience at the Alex Theater in Glendale, CA.
